cornet rilkes song of love and death is a 
beautiful opera by siegfried matthus 
an hour and a half long it was given its american premiere by 
students of the manhattan school of music 
when matthus called the most often performed living german 
opera composer had his first american opera debut of judith 
last summer in santa fe nm he was an east german he attended 
both that premiere and cornet rilke on wednesday night here 
judith depicting a story from biblical times is exceeding 
tense musically and dramatically cornet rilke though matthus 
means it as an antiwar piece soars with youth and promise and 
lovely melodies 
the students all had pleasing voices capable of singing the 
music but almost none of the english translation was 
understandable except that of the 30member chorus david gilbert 
conducted the orchestra of 15 
matthus bases his opera on an 1899 epic poem by rainer maria 
rilke about a person in his family tree who died at 18 fighting the 
turks since the opera reopened the dresden opera house in 1985 
burned 40 years before matthus begins it with the chorus singing 
on such a night there once was a fire a lament for the opera 
house and for the young rilke 
tattered curtains pull away showing the youths body on the 
ground staging using a diagonal ramp and imaginative lighting 
was telling throughout near the end the chorus holds pieces of 
wall which reflect the fire 
the opera is in a number of concise scenes each ending in 
blackout every detail and bit of music works toward the whole 
effect at first soldiers on their way to battle make horseback 
riding motions as they sing putting a foot down then bending 
their knees twice before stepping again they sing of mothers and 
wives at one point are met by tarts 
rilke finds a mans body a woman tied to a tree is promoted to 
cornet meaning standard bearer the part is written for a woman 
womens light voices sound younger than tenors christine abraham 
sang rilke and lisa livingston walking behind like a shadow sang 
a larger part rilkes thoughts 
the soldiers are given a party at a castle and the countess 
seduces rilke 
the next morning the boy joyfully awakened to the 
possibilities of adulthood grabs the flag and runs into battle 
where he is stabbed to death 
musical styles change depending on moods of scene sometimes 
there is melody in the orchestra but modernsounding angularities 
for the singers the love scenes music is tenderly melodic instead 
of passionate at the end drums roll 
