<TEXT>
the city council voted to abolish bostons 
13member school board accusing it of ripping off the 
taxpayers and failing to educate the citys children the move 
needs the approval of the governor and legislature 
the city council approved 103 wednesday a measure to put 
education of the citys 57000 public school children under the 
direct control of the council and mayor raymond flynn 
flynn said legislative approval would put boston in the 
forefront of education reform 
the school committee as the elected board is known had been 
criticized for failing to find a new superintendent last week it 
called off its eightmonth search 
the quality of the citys schools had also come under attack as 
had the boards failure to close a 12 million deficit in this 
years 3895 million budget 
the school committee over there has been ripping off the 
taxpayers unmercifully said councilman albert dapper oneil 
today is dday 
no matter what the particular issue nothing happens or if it 
happens its done in an incorrect way said councilman james 
byrne who proposed abolishing the board 
