<TEXT>
president hussain muhammad ershad 
resigned today and surrendered power to an oppositionnominated 
political independent who will lead the country until elections 
promised for within three months 
ershad a former army general who held power for eight years 
agreed on tuesday to step down after a sevenweek campaign of large 
street protests that grew only fiercer when he imposed a state of 
emergency last week 
fulfilling a vow he made to opposition leaders ershad 
administered the oath of office to shahabuddin ahmed chief justice 
of the supreme court 
ershad then resigned as president of this impoverished nation of 
107 million people 
allah bless you ershad told shahabuddin you have our 
blessings i want peace to return to the society 
shahabuddin sworn in as vice president will serve as acting 
president and preside over new elections that are to be held within 
90 days 
i have no political ambition i shall not stay here beyond the 
mandated 90 days shahabuddin told opposition leaders after the 
ceremony 
during this period i shall try to ensure peace and stability 
hold free and fair elections and hand over power to the elected 
representatives of the people he said 
the transfer of power was shown on staterun television 
ershad wearing a black suit and looking grim was flanked by 
the chiefs of the army navy and air force it was the first time 
he had appeared on television since monday night when he first 
expressed a willingness to resign 
the ceremony took place at the presidents office inside dhakas 
military cantonment a wellguarded complex of offices and houses 
ershad 60 was an army general when he seized in a 1982 
bloodless coup he resigned his military commission before running 
the 1986 presidential election that opponents said he stole through 
massive voterigging 
shahabuddin 62 met the opposition leaders later in the day 
originally his nomination was to be approved by parliament on 
saturday but ershad unexpectedly dissolved the lawmaking body this 
morning 
