<TEXT>
president hussain muhammad ershad 
resigned thursday after ruling the country for eight years handing 
power to an interim leader chosen by the opposition 
ershad a former army general who took power in a 1982 coup had 
faced seven weeks of often violent nationwide protests against his 
government on tuesday he promised to step down as soon as a 
replacement was named 
earlier thursday ershad lifted the state of emergency in effect 
since nov 27 
later he administered the oath of office to shahabuddin ahmed 
a political independent nominated by the countrys opposition 
parties as caretaker vicepresident then he signed a letter of 
resignation making him acting president 
allah bless you he told shahabuddin after the 15minute 
ceremony in the presidents office you have our blessings i 
want peace to return to society 
originally shahabuddins nomination was to be approved by 
parliament on saturday but ershad unexpectedly dissolved the 
lawmaking body early thursday 
constitutional experts and opposition sources said it had been 
doubtful that a majority of legislators would emerge in public for 
a vote twothirds of parliament belonged to ershads jatiya party 
and many were reluctant to appear in public for fear of being 
attacked by antiershad activists 
shahabuddin 62 chief justice of the supreme court will 
supervise elections to parliament which must be reconstituted 
within 90 days the new body will decide whether to retain power or 
hold presidential elections 
i have no political ambition i shall not stay here beyond the 
mandated 90 days said shahbuddin 62 after he was sworn in 
during this period i shall try to ensure peace and stability 
hold free and fair elections and hand over power to the elected 
representatives of the people 
reporters who attended the transfer of power ceremony said 
ershads eyes were filled with tears as he bade farewell to chiefs 
of the countrys army navy and air force and his personal staff 
army chief lt gen nooruddin khan played a pivotal role in 
persuading ershad to resign according to wellplaced sources he 
acted as a middleman between the president and the opposition after 
junior army officers advised khan they would not support a man 
opposed by the people the sources said 
after thursdays ceremony ershad and khan shook hands and 
embraced ershad then left for his home 
ershad was the army chief when he took power in a bloodless coup 
eight years ago he resigned from the army after winning 
presidential elections in 1986 which the opposition claimed were 
rigged 
charges of vote fraud also dogged the 1986 and 1988 elections to 
parliament which were won by ershads jatiya or peoples party 
the opposition made vote fraud the pivotal point of their protest 
campaign when ershad announced his candidacy for the june 1991 
presidential poll 
ershads resignation capped a dizzying reversal of his political 
fortunes three weeks ago he was confidently predicting success in 
next years presidential elections 
the opposition campaign to oust him had long been little more 
than an irritation during his rule of this impoverished nation of 
107 million people 
but it gained new impetus with the end of longstanding political 
differences between sheik hasina and khaleda zia the opposition 
leaders its growth continued even after ershad declared the state 
of emergency in late november and called out the army to quell 
street protests 
hundreds of doctors professors merchant seamen civil servants 
and some jatiya party members of parliament resigned to back the 
opposition call on monday ershad offered to resign 45 days before 
the next presidential polls the opposition rejected the offer and 
intensified its protest campaign 
then on tuesday night ershad promised to resign immediately 
one of his last acts before resigning was to withdraw the state 
of emergency and restore civil rights the opposition claims that 
at least 100 people were killed by government troops during the 
emergency ershads administration said only six people had died 
the choice of shahabuddin to head the interim government was 
made by ms hasina and mrs zia 
ms hasina leader of the leftofcenter awami league is the 
daughter of sheik mujibur rahman bangladeshs first president 
mrs zia head of the bangladesh nationalist party is the widow 
of another former president ziaur rahman both men were 
assassinated 
ershad is the countrys ninth president since it gained 
independence from pakistan in 1971 all were installed by military 
action 
