proposes new spending will at a disadvantage but thats a big if 
we havent seen that before 
cbo director robert reischauer warned the house budget committee 
that with the economy continuing to worsen next years shortfall 
could well be even worse than 337 billion as the economy 
declines the government collects less revenue and spends more for 
unemployment and other programs driving up the deficit 
reischauer told the lawmakers that he expected the economy to 
shrink during the last three months of 1990 and that the same 
thing would probably happen during the first quarter of 1991 if the 
large us troop deployment in the middle east continues but he 
did predict an improving economy beginning in 1992 and a shrinking 
federal deficit 
it looks like a period of weakness followed by a rebound 
he said 
this years budget gap should be 320 billion the cbo said 
fiscal 1991 runs through next sept 30 
the deficit for fiscal 1990 was 220 billion just below the 
record 221 billion shortfall in 1986 
those figures cannot be directly compared with the 320 billion 
projection for next year 
past years deficits included the huge and growing social 
