alan bond the flamboyant businessman 
who bought a van gogh and bankrolled a stunning yachting upset was 
charged today in connection with a government investigation of a 
collapsed investment bank 
bond whose brewing and mining empire collapsed in a mountain of 
some 6 billion in debt joins a growing list of fallen australian 
highflyers now facing criminal charges 
he was accused of concealing information during an attempted 
1987 rescue of the investment bank rothwells ltd police in perth 
bonds hometown said bond was released on 77000 bail he was to 
appear in court on friday 
in a statement bond denied the allegations saying he is 
absolutely innocent 
bond was charged in an investigation by a special government 
task force set up rothwells collapsed in november 1988 with losses 
of about 200 million 
police last week charged former rothwells chief laurie connell 
and casino boss dallas dempster for alleged illegal stock trading 
three others face trial on charges of falsifying accounts to make 
it appear the bank was making substantial profits 
prosecutors allege that large undisclosed borrowing by connell 
of up to 385 million was the main cause of rothwells failure 
bond joins bankrupt hooker corp head george herscu and elders 
resources managing director geoff lord as prominent australian 
businessmen to face criminal charges 
herscu one of australias 10 richest men until hooker corp 
fell on hard times was convicted thursday of corruption charges 
for paying off a former state official on monday lord was charged 
with 37 similar offenses 
the charge against bond a britishborn former signpainter was 
the latest chapter in a long slide 
only three years ago bond bought vincent van goghs irises 
from the auction house sothebys for a thenrecord 539 million 
the same yeat he financed australias upset of the united states in 
the americass cup yacht race 
at its peak bond corp holdings ltd the company he founded 
included interests in brewing media resources and property it 
had a gold mine and telephone company holdings in chile and 
brewing and other mining interests in the united states 
australian prime minister bob hawke last year praised bond as 
a great australian 
bond rode out the 1987 stockmarket crash on strong cash flow 
from his beer assets but the man who built a fortune on borrowed 
funds continued to overextend and bond corp eventually ran up 
estimated debts of more than 6 billion 
a combination of heavy debts rising interest rates and bad 
business decisions alienated bankers and creditors put bonds 
australian brewing interests into receivership and forced him to 
sell assets ranging from a hong kong office development to a coal 
mine 
in march bond sold the van gogh for an undisclosed amount amid 
reports he had taken a loss 
in september he resigned under pressure as chairman and 
director of bond corp although he still holds a controlling 
interest through his private company dallhold investments two 
days after the resignation bond corp reported a loss of 172 
billion 
bond was charged under the western australia state securities 
industry code with concealing an arrangement between rothwells and 
bond corp from another member of the rescue team 
under the deal bond corp was to contribute 131 million to a 
rescue package aimed at keeping rothwells afloat after the october 
1987 stock market crash caused a run on its funds 
but bond allegedly did not tell other contributors he was to 
receive a 123 million fee for helping to organize the rescue 
the charge alleges that by concealing the arrangement bond 
induced perth businessman brian coppin to contribute to the rescue 
through an underwriting agreement with wardley australia securities 
ltd 
i deny absolutely that i acted dishonestly or concealed 
anything from brian coppin bonds statements said 
he said no fee was paid to me bond corp holdings ltd or 
any company associated with me in connection with the rothwells 
rescue of 1987 i am absolutely innocent of any wrongdoing and the 
charge will be strenuously defended 
