<TEXT>
american telephone and telegraph co has filed 
federal lawsuits in maryland and ohio seeking to block ncr corp 
from fighting a hostile 61 billion takeover attempt by the 
telephone giant 
atampt spokeswoman paula horii said the lawsuit filed thursday in 
us district court in columbus ohio seeks to prevent ncr from 
stalling atampt with requests for information 
the baltimore action filed late wednesday in us district 
court also names ncr which is chartered in maryland and maryland 
attorney general j joseph curran who has opposed corporate 
takeovers 
atampt asked a federal judge to bar ncr and curran from using the 
maryland business combination act or other state laws to stop atampt 
from acquiring enough ncr stock or shareholder proxies to take 
over the dayon ohiobased computer maker 
the maryland law would impose a fiveyear moratorium on 
acquiring enough stock or proxies to force a takeover 
atampt has issued a tender offer of 90 per share for ncr common 
stock which the lawsuit said is a premium of nearly 90 percent 
over the market price of ncrs common shares 
ncr chairman charles e exley has told atampt his company would 
not consider a tender offer of less than 125 per share 
ncr spokeswoman connie olasz said the company has not yet seen 
the lawsuits and could not comment on them 
olasz said ncrs board of directors on wednesday voted to opt 
out of a maryland state law in an attempt to block atampt from 
calling a special meeting of ncr shareholders to vote on the tender 
offer 
</TEXT>
